edu.ucsd.cse232b.jsidrach.xquery

Class XQueryVisitor

  • java.lang.Object
    • <any>
      • edu.ucsd.cse232b.jsidrach.xquery.XQueryVisitor

  • public class XQueryVisitor
extends <any>
    XQueryVisitor - Visitor for the context tree generated by ANTLR4

    The traversal of the context tree has to be done manually, recursively calling visit(ctx)
    Initially, the root of the grammar is invoked
    Each method modifies the current list of nodes (nodes) and returns it

   → ∃ x ∈ [rp_1](n) ∃ y ∈ [rp_2](n) / x is y
        Note: filter functions should not change the current list of nodes
        Parameters:
        ctx - Current parse tree context
        Returns:
        Current list of nodes if there exists some x in the first relative path and some y in the second relative path that reference the same node - an empty list otherwise
